<h1 id="supports-color">supports-color <a href="https://travis-ci.org/chalk/supports-color"><img alt="Build Status" src="https://travis-ci.org/chalk/supports-color.svg?branch=master" /></a></h1>

<blockquote>
<p>Detect whether a terminal supports color</p>
</blockquote>

<h2 id="install">Install</h2>
<pre class="highlight plaintext"><code>$ npm install --save supports-color
</code></pre>

<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>
<pre class="highlight javascript"><code><span class="kd">var</span> <span class="nx">supportsColor</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">require</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'supports-color'</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="nx">supportsColor</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="nx">console</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">log</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'Terminal supports color'</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="p">}</span>
</code></pre>

<p>It obeys the <code class="prettyprint">--color</code> and <code class="prettyprint">--no-color</code> CLI flags.</p>

<p>For situations where using <code class="prettyprint">--color</code> is not possible, add an environment variable <code class="prettyprint">FORCE_COLOR</code> with any value to force color. Trumps <code class="prettyprint">--no-color</code>.</p>

